The Vice President released a statement in response to the Supreme Court's decision in Obergefell v. Hodges, which legalized same-sex marriage in the United States. The Vice President expressed pride in the decision, stating that it affirms the civil rights and equal protection of same-sex couples. He also highlighted the years of discrimination and stigma faced by the LGBTQ+ community and acknowledged the courage of those who fought for marriage equality. The Vice President emphasized that this decision is a step towards treating all people with respect and dignity.